{
  "stem": "8703.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of them was working for my-- for my uncle, and they behaved very nice with at night.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They shared even cigarettes with me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's all I, I, I had.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then we came closer in 1942.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A resistance-- we started to organize.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Polish organized.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We could not compare with the Polish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Number one, they were free-- free to go from one city to the other.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A Jew was not allowed to go out from, from the ghetto even.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had-- they had weapons from before the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were hiding some of the weapons.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Jewish people didn't-- they didn't have any weapons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They went to the army.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They went to the army.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had ones before the war-- a gun, a Betar party that I used to belong.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But where, who had it, where it wind up, I don't know who had it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The resistance-- I had a steady contact with the Polish resistance.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Not everybody, not every Jew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I had a very good friend, a Polish man, who went to school with me together.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We played together Polish theater.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we became friends.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he was active in the Polish underground.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I was-- and he supplied all the publications that the underground published at the time illegally.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And you know, they, they were-- they were bringing what they are doing, what kind of activities, that they are blowing up trains, that they are-- that they are attacking or you know, the German police, and sabotage ops.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was informed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I used to help.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But one thing I will never forget.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was in August, the beginning of September.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Beginning of September, I believe it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It comes after they liquidated Kielce.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Kielce was a big city, about 30,000 Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
